---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';

const updated = new Date('2026-06-25').toLocaleDateString('en-US', {
  year: 'numeric',
  month: 'long',
  day: 'numeric',
});
---
<BaseLayout
  title="Privacy & Cookies | Control Resonant Field Guide"
  description="How controlresonant.wiki handles analytics, cookies, and your data — in plain language."
>
  <section class="border-b border-ash-700">
    <div class="wrap py-12">
      <p class="eyebrow">File Metadata</p>
      <h1 class="mt-3 font-display text-3xl font-bold text-bone sm:text-4xl">Privacy &amp; Cookies</h1>
      <p class="mt-4 font-mono text-[0.62rem] uppercase tracking-[0.14em] text-ash-500">Last updated {updated}</p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <div class="wrap py-12">
    <div class="prose-doc">
      <p>
        This page explains, in plain terms, what data controlresonant.wiki collects and why. The
        short version: we don't ask you to create an account, and we don't sell your personal
        information.
      </p>

      <h2>Analytics</h2>
      <p>
        We use privacy-conscious web analytics to understand which pages are useful and how the
        site performs. This is aggregate data — page views, rough geographic region, device type,
        and referrer. It is not used to personally identify you.
      </p>

      <h2>Cookies</h2>
      <p>
        The site may set a small number of cookies to support analytics and remember basic
        display preferences. You can block or clear cookies at any time in your browser settings;
        the guides will still work.
      </p>

      <h2>Third parties</h2>
      <p>
        Some features rely on third-party services — for example, fonts and analytics — which may
        process limited technical data such as your IP address to deliver their service. If
        advertising is introduced in the future, this section will be updated to describe it and
        any related choices before it goes live.
      </p>

      <h2>Affiliate links</h2>
      <p>
        Where the site links to a storefront, that link may occasionally be an affiliate link,
        meaning we could earn a small commission if you buy something. It never changes the price
        you pay, and it never influences what we report about the game.
      </p>

      <h2>Contact</h2>
      <p>
        Questions about privacy, or want data about your visit addressed? Reach out through the
        contact details on the <a href="/about/">about page</a>.
      </p>
    </div>
  </div>
</BaseLayout>
